+# Green Contract Testing Framework Design
+
+## Overview
+
+The Green Contract framework provides a contract testing approach where test suites are defined as executable contracts with 5 severity levels.
+
+## GreenLevel Enum
+
+```typescript
+enum GreenLevel {
+  /** Critical: All tests must pass or the build fails */
+  CRITICAL = 0,
+  /** High: Tests should pass; failures are serious */
+  HIGH = 1,
+  /** Medium: Tests should pass; failures are notable */
+  MEDIUM = 2,
+  /** Low: Tests run but failures are warnings only */
+  LOW = 3,
+  /** Info: Tests run for visibility; failures don't affect result */
+  INFO = 4,
+}
+```
+
+## GreenContract Definition
+
+```typescript
+interface GreenContract {
+  id: string;
+  name: string;
+  description: string;
+  level: GreenLevel;
+  tags?: string[];
+  setup?: () => Promise<void> | void;
+  teardown?: () => Promise<void> | void;
+  test: () => Promise<TestResult> | TestResult;
+}
+
+interface TestResult {
+  passed: boolean;
+  message?: string;
+  durationMs?: number;
+  artifacts?: TestArtifact[];
+  subResults?: TestResult[];
+}
+
+interface TestArtifact {
+  type: "screenshot" | "log" | "data" | "file";
+  name: string;
+  path?: string;
+  content?: string;
+  url?: string;
+}
+```
+
+## Core Components
+
+### GreenContractEvaluator
+
+```typescript
+class GreenContractEvaluator {
+  private contracts = new Map<string, GreenContract>();
+
+  register(contract: GreenContract): void;
+  unregister(contractId: string): boolean;
+  getContract(id: string): GreenContract | undefined;
+  listContracts(filter?: { level?: GreenLevel; tags?: string[] }): GreenContract[];
+  evaluate(contractId: string): Promise<TestResult>;
+  evaluateAll(filter?: { level?: GreenLevel; tags?: string[] }): Promise<EvaluationSummary>;
+}
+```
+
+### TestResultCollector
+
+```typescript
+interface EvaluationSummary {
+  total: number;
+  passed: number;
+  failed: number;
+  skipped: number;
+  durationMs: number;
+  results: ContractResult[];
+  failures: ContractResult[];
+}
+
+interface ContractResult {
+  contractId: string;
+  contractName: string;
+  level: GreenLevel;
+  result: TestResult;
+}
+
+class TestResultCollector {
+  private results: ContractResult[] = [];
+
+  addResult(result: ContractResult): void;
+  getResults(): ContractResult[];
+  getFailures(): ContractResult[];
+  getSummary(): EvaluationSummary;
+  clear(): void;
+  serialize(): string;
+}
+```
+
+### RegressionRunner
+
+```typescript
+interface RegressionOptions {
+  /** Only run contracts at or above this level */
+  minLevel?: GreenLevel;
+  /** Only run contracts with these tags */
+  tags?: string[];
+  /** Parallel execution count */
+  concurrency?: number;
+  /** Timeout per contract in ms */
+  timeoutMs?: number;
+  /** Continue on failure */
+  failFast?: boolean;
+  /** Baseline results to compare against */
+  baseline?: EvaluationSummary;
+}
+
+class RegressionRunner {
+  constructor(
+    private evaluator: GreenContractEvaluator,
+    private collector: TestResultCollector,
+  );
+
+  run(options?: RegressionOptions): Promise<EvaluationSummary>;
+  runBaseline(): Promise<EvaluationSummary>;
+  compareWithBaseline(summary: EvaluationSummary): RegressionDiff;
+}
+
+interface RegressionDiff {
+  newFailures: string[];
+  fixedFailures: string[];
+  stillFailing: string[];
+  regressions: { contractId: string; before: boolean; after: boolean }[];
+}
+```
+
+## Level-Based Exit Behavior
+
+| Level | Exit Code | Behavior |
+|-------|-----------|----------|
+| CRITICAL | 1 | Fail build immediately |
+| HIGH | 1 | Fail build but can be overridden |
+| MEDIUM | 0 | Warning logged |
+| LOW | 0 | Warning logged |
+| INFO | 0 | No effect |
+
+## Implementation Files
+
+| File | Purpose |
+|------|---------|
+| `src/testing/green-contract/types.ts` | GreenLevel, GreenContract, TestResult types |
+| `src/testing/green-contract/evaluator.ts` | GreenContractEvaluator |
+| `src/testing/green-contract/collector.ts` | TestResultCollector |
+| `src/testing/green-contract/runner.ts` | RegressionRunner |
+| `src/testing/green-contract/index.ts` | Public API exports |
