+# MCP Integration Enhancement Design
+
+## Overview
+
+Enhanced MCP (Model Context Protocol) integration for OpenClaw with Tool Registry, Permission Policy Engine, and MCP Server Registry.
+
+## Milestone 1: Tool Registry System
+
+### ToolMetadata Schema
+
+```typescript
+interface ToolMetadata {
+  name: string;
+  description: string;
+  category: "filesystem" | "network" | "process" | "computation" | "communication";
+  tags: string[];
+  inputSchema: Record<string, unknown>;
+  outputSchema?: Record<string, unknown>;
+  capabilities: ToolCapability[];
+  riskLevel: "low" | "medium" | "high" | "critical";
+  deprecationNotice?: string;
+}
+
+type ToolCapability =
+  | { kind: "file-read"; paths?: string[] }
+  | { kind: "file-write"; paths?: string[] }
+  | { kind: "network-http"; methods?: string[]; hosts?: string[] }
+  | { kind: "network-https"; methods?: string[]; hosts?: string[] }
+  | { kind: "process-spawn"; command?: string }
+  | { kind: "process-exec" };
+```
+
+### ToolRegistry Class
+
+- `registerTool(metadata: ToolMetadata): void`
+- `getTool(name: string): ToolMetadata | undefined`
+- `listTools(filter?: Partial<ToolMetadata>): ToolMetadata[]`
+- `unregisterTool(name: string): boolean`
+- `updateTool(name: string, metadata: Partial<ToolMetadata>): boolean`
+
+## Milestone 2: Permission Policy Engine
+
+### Policy Types
+
+```typescript
+type PolicyEffect = "allow" | "deny" | "prompt";
+
+interface PermissionPolicy {
+  id: string;
+  name: string;
+  description: string;
+  target: PolicyTarget;
+  effect: PolicyEffect;
+  conditions?: PolicyCondition[];
+  priority: number;
+}
+
+type PolicyTarget =
+  | { type: "tool"; toolName: string }
+  | { type: "category"; category: ToolMetadata["category"] }
+  | { type: "tag"; tag: string }
+  | { type: "risk-level"; level: ToolMetadata["riskLevel"] };
+
+type PolicyCondition =
+  | { kind: "always" }
+  | { kind: "never" }
+  | { kind: "boolean"; flag: string }
+  | { kind: "time-range"; start: string; end: string }
+  | { kind: "path-match"; paths: string[]; pattern: string };
+```
+
+### PolicyEngine Class
+
+- `evaluatePermission(toolName: string, context: PermissionContext): PolicyResult>`
+- `addPolicy(policy: PermissionPolicy): void`
+- `removePolicy(policyId: string): boolean`
+- `listPolicies(): PermissionPolicy[]`
+
+## Milestone 3: MCP Server Registry
+
+### ServerState Enum
+
+```typescript
+enum ServerState {
+  STOPPED = "stopped",
+  STARTING = "starting",
+  RUNNING = "running",
+  STOPPING = "stopping",
+  ERROR = "error",
+}
+```
+
+### McpServerRegistry Class
+
+- `registerServer(id: string, config: McpServerConfig): void`
+- `unregisterServer(id: string): boolean`
+- `startServer(id: string): Promise<void>`
+- `stopServer(id: string): Promise<void>`
+- `getServerState(id: string): ServerState`
+- `listServers(): McpServerDescriptor[]`
+
+## Implementation Files
+
+| File | Purpose |
+|------|---------|
+| `src/mcp/tool-registry.ts` | Tool Registry with metadata schema |
+| `src/mcp/permission-policy.ts` | Permission Policy Engine |
+| `src/mcp/server-registry.ts` | MCP Server Registry |
+| `src/mcp/index.ts` | Public API exports |
