@@ -0,0 +1,118 @@
+/**
+ * OpenClaw Memory & Context System Enhancement Design
+ * ===================================================
+ *
+ * This design document outlines the enhanced memory and context management
+ * system for OpenClaw, inspired by Claude Code's compaction architecture.
+ *
+ * ## Memory Four-Type Classification
+ * -----------------------------------
+ * Memory entries are classified into four types with distinct characteristics:
+ *
+ * 1. **user** - User-specific context (preferences, ongoing projects, personal info)
+ *    - Priority: HIGH
+ *    - Persistence: Long-term, rarely invalidated
+ *    - Frontmatter: type, created, tags, priority
+ *
+ * 2. **feedback** - Conversation feedback and corrections
+ *    - Priority: MEDIUM-HIGH
+ *    - Persistence: Session-based, can persist across sessions with explicit learning
+ *    - Frontmatter: type, sessionId, turnIndex, feedbackType
+ *
+ * 3. **project** - Project-specific context (code patterns, architecture decisions)
+ *    - Priority: MEDIUM
+ *    - Persistence: Project-scoped, invalidated when project changes
+ *    - Frontmatter: type, projectId, scope, technologies
+ *
+ * 4. **reference** - Reference materials, documentation, external knowledge
+ *    - Priority: LOW-MEDIUM
+ *    - Persistence: Long-term but periodically refreshed
+ *    - Frontmatter: type, source, lastRefreshed, relevance
+ *
+ * ## Frontmatter Format
+ * --------------------
+ * All memory entries use YAML frontmatter:
+ *
+ * ```yaml
+ * ---
+ * type: user|feedback|project|reference
+ * created: ISO8601 timestamp
+ * updated: ISO8601 timestamp
+ * tags: [tag1, tag2]
+ * priority: high|medium|low
+ * ---
+ * ```
+ *
+ * Additional type-specific fields are documented below.
+ *
+ * ## Multi-Level Compaction Architecture
+ * --------------------------------------
+ * Implements a four-tier progressive compaction system:
+ *
+ * 1. **HistorySnip** (L1 - Passive)
+ *    - Trigger: Message count exceeds threshold (default: 50 messages)
+ *    - Action: Remove oldest assistant thinking blocks, truncate tool results
+ *    - Tokens saved: ~10-20% of head context
+ *    - Preservation: Full message structure maintained
+ *
+ * 2. **Microcompact** (L2 - Passive)
+ *    - Trigger: Time-based (default: 30 min gap since last assistant message)
+ *    - Action: Content-clear old tool results, keep recent N tool results
+ *    - Tokens saved: ~30-50% of tool result content
+ *    - Preservation: Tool structure maintained, content replaced with stub
+ *
+ * 3. **ContextCollapse** (L3 - Active)
+ *    - Trigger: Token count exceeds 90% of effective context window
+ *    - Action: Summarize middle third of conversation, preserve head and tail
+ *    - Tokens saved: ~60-70% of summarized portion
+ *    - Preservation: Creates summary with preserved segment metadata
+ *
+ * 4. **AutoCompact** (L4 - Reactive)
+ *    - Trigger: Token count exceeds auto-compact threshold (default: 87% of window)
+ *    - Action: Full conversation summary, boundary marker inserted
+ *    - Tokens saved: ~80-90% of original context
+ *    - Preservation: Single summary replaces all messages before boundary
+ *
+ * ## Context Assembly Optimization
+ * -------------------------------
+ * Smart context assembly with the following strategies:
+ *
+ * 1. **Token Budget Control**
+ *    - Hard limit: tokenBudget parameter (if provided)
+ *    - Soft limit: auto-compact threshold minus buffer
+ *    - Priority ordering: system > memory > recent messages > historical
+ *
+ * 2. **Priority-Based Ordering**
+ *    - Priority 1: System prompt + runtime instructions
+ *    - Priority 2: User memory (type=user)
+ *    - Priority 3: Project context (type=project)
+ *    - Priority 4: Recent conversation (last N turns)
+ *    - Priority 5: Feedback entries (type=feedback)
+ *    - Priority 6: Reference materials (type=reference)
+ *
+ * 3. **Tool Result Truncation Strategy**
+ *    - Truncate from the middle of long tool results
+ *    - Preserve first N lines (command echo, important output head)
+ *    - Preserve last N lines (important final output)
+ *    - Insert [...] marker in truncated middle
+ *    - Per-tool-result budget: default 2000 tokens
+ *
+ * ## Implementation Files
+ * -----------------------
+ * - context-engine/types.ts - Extended type definitions
+ * - context-engine/memory/ - Memory management module
+ *   - types.ts - Memory entry types with frontmatter
+ *   - store.ts - Memory store implementation
+ *   - frontmatter.ts - Frontmatter parsing/serialization
+ *   - classifier.ts - Memory type classification
+ * - context-engine/compact/ - Compaction module
+ *   - index.ts - Compaction orchestrator
+ *   - historySnip.ts - L1 HistorySnip compaction
+ *   - microCompact.ts - L2 Microcompact (from Claude Code)
+ *   - contextCollapse.ts - L3 ContextCollapse
+ *   - autoCompact.ts - L4 AutoCompact
+ *   - tokenBudget.ts - Token budget management
+ * - context-engine/assemble.ts - Context assembly with optimization
+ */
+
+
