+# Task System Design
+
+## Overview
+
+The OpenClaw Task System provides a unified abstraction for tracking and managing background work units across different execution environments.
+
+## Task Type System
+
+### TaskRuntime Types
+
+The `TaskRuntime` enum defines 7 execution environments:
+
+| Runtime | Description |
+|---------|-------------|
+| `local_bash` | Local shell command execution via exec tool |
+| `remote_agent` | Remote agent execution via network protocol |
+| `in_process_teammate` | In-process teammate (same process, async) |
+| `subagent` | Subagent spawned as separate session/process |
+| `acp` | Agent Communication Protocol background task |
+| `cli` | CLI command execution |
+| `cron` | Scheduled/cron-based task |
+
+### Task ID Encoding
+
+Task IDs follow the format: `tsk_<base62_timestamp>_<base62_random>`
+
+- `tsk_` prefix identifies the type
+- `base62_timestamp`: Unix timestamp in milliseconds, base62 encoded (10 chars)
+- `base62_random`: 12 chars of cryptographically random base62
+
+Example: `tsk_4k8m9p1q2_7x3n5p8z1`
+
+The encoding allows:
+- Task ID prefix matching for scanning
+- Time-based ordering (earlier tasks have lexicographically smaller IDs)
+- Collision resistance via random component
+
+### TaskStatus State Machine
+
+```
+     ┌─────────┐
+     │ queued  │
+     └────┬────┘
+          │ start
+          ▼
+     ┌─────────┐
+     │ running │
+     └────┬────┘
+          │
+    ┌─────┴─────┐
+    │           │
+    ▼           ▼
+┌────────┐  ┌────────┐
+│succeeded│  │ failed │
+└────────┘  └────────┘
+    ▲           ▲
+    │           │
+    └─────┬─────┘
+          │
+    ┌─────┴─────┐
+    │           │
+    ▼           ▼
+┌─────────┐ ┌────────┐
+│timed_out│ │cancelled│
+└─────────┘ └────────┘
+    ▲
+    │ timeout
+    └────────── (from running)
+
+┌────────┐
+│  lost  │ (session disappeared unexpectedly)
+└────────┘
+```
+
+#### Terminal States
+
+A task reaches a terminal state when `isTerminalTaskStatus(status)` returns true:
+- `succeeded` - Task completed successfully
+- `failed` - Task failed with error
+- `timed_out` - Task exceeded timeout
+- `cancelled` - Task was explicitly cancelled
+- `lost` - Backing session/agent disappeared
+
+#### Terminal Outcome
+
+`TaskTerminalOutcome` indicates the semantic result:
+- `succeeded` - Task achieved its goal
+- `blocked` - Task was blocked (e.g., by policy, auth, or dependency)
+
+## Task Hierarchy
+
+Tasks support parent-child relationships via:
+- `parentTaskId` - Direct parent task
+- `parentFlowId` - Parent flow (for orchestrated multi-task flows)
+
+## Unified Task API
+
+### Core Functions
+
+```typescript
+// Create a new task
+createTaskRecord(params: CreateTaskParams): TaskRecord
+
+// State transitions
+markTaskRunningByRunId(params: MarkRunningParams): TaskRecord[]
+markTaskTerminalByRunId(params: MarkTerminalParams): TaskRecord[]
+markTaskTerminalById(params: MarkTerminalByIdParams): TaskRecord | null
+
+// Queries
+getTaskById(taskId: string): TaskRecord | undefined
+findTaskByRunId(runId: string): TaskRecord | undefined
+listTasksForSessionKey(sessionKey: string): TaskRecord[]
+listTasksForFlowId(flowId: string): TaskRecord[]
+listTaskRecords(): TaskRecord[]
+
+// Lifecycle
+cancelTaskById(params: CancelParams): Promise<CancelResult>
+setTaskProgressById(params: ProgressParams): TaskRecord | null
+
+// Utilities
+isTerminalTaskStatus(status: TaskStatus): boolean
+resolveTaskTerminalOutcome(task: TaskRecord): TaskTerminalOutcome | undefined
+```
+
+### Persistence
+
+Tasks are persisted via `TaskRegistryStore`:
+- In-memory default for development
+- SQLite-based store for production (`task-registry.store.sqlite.ts`)
+- Automatic snapshot on registry changes
+
+## Implementation Files
+
+| File | Purpose |
+|------|---------|
+| `task-registry.types.ts` | Type definitions (TaskRecord, TaskRuntime, TaskStatus, etc.) |
+| `task-registry.ts` | Core registry implementation |
+| `task-executor.ts` | Task execution orchestration |
+| `task-executor-policy.ts` | Delivery and notification policies |
+| `task-status.ts` | Status formatting utilities |
+| `task-id.ts` | Task ID generation and parsing |
+| `runtime-internal.ts` | Public API re-exports |
+| `task-registry.store.ts` | Store interface |
+| `task-registry.store.sqlite.ts` | SQLite persistence |
